<title>FRANCE: Sanofi up on smell of Ricci sale.</title>
<headline>Sanofi up on smell of Ricci sale.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-07-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in French health and beauty products group Sanofi made further gains on Wednesday after a 5.54 percent rise on Tuesday on an expected sale of its stake in Nina Ricci perfumes.</p>
<p>The company said on Tuesday it was willing to sell its 49.9 percent stake in loss-making Ricci if majority owners the Ruch family would sell as well.</p>
<p>The announcement raised speculation of a further restructuring in the Sanofi perfumes business, which includes Yves Saint Laurent, Oscar de la Renta, Roger &amp; Gallet and Van Cleef &amp; Arpels.</p>
<p>At 0900 GMT, Sanofi was up 4.75 percent at 639 francs.</p>
